title: Coffee Lake
summary: Coffee Lake is Intel's codename for its eighth generation Core microprocessor family, announced on September 25, 2017.[5] It is manufactured using Intel's second 14Â nm process node refinement.[6] Desktop Coffee Lake processors introduced i5 and i7 CPUs featuring six cores (along with hyper-threading in the case of the latter) and Core i3 CPUs with four cores and no hyperthreading.
